            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1587156389167-best-practices-for-alt-text-descriptions" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#34953ac3-d392-4042-b607-905f3aab91a9" href="#accordion-content-1587156389167-best-practices-for-alt-text-descriptions" aria-controls="accordion-content-1587156389167-best-practices-for-alt-text-descriptions" aria-expanded="false">
                            Best practices for alt text descriptions
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1587156389167-best-practices-for-alt-text-descriptions" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1587156389167-best-practices-for-alt-text-descriptions">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1587156389167 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resReference section">

























<div class="restext resText parbase">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="a002fb73-3fa4-48cd-b6bc-439005463484" >

    <ul> 
 <li>Alternative text should be concise and meaningful.</li> 
 <li>Usually around a sentence or two.&nbsp;</li> 
 <li>Use punctuation, as it can help make information easier to understand.</li> 
 <li>Avoid phrases such as "image of…" or "graphic of…"</li> 
 <li>Consider the context of the surrounding information when writing.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>For more guidance on alternative text concepts and how to use correctly, please visit&nbsp;<a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/tutorials/images/">W3C's Images Tutorial.<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a></p>
    





</div>
